text.section:
"Governmental entity" means a special taxing district which:
Is a unit of government responsible for an area situated solely within a single county;
Has a governing body elected independently of the county government;
Is financed with revenues secured in whole or in part from special taxes or assessments levied on real property situated within the area;
Performs municipal services for the residents of the area; and
Was not created for a limited or special purpose or purposes.
